# Capsule runtime scripts execute on Linux (in the MicroVM) — they MUST be LF, or a
# CRLF shebang becomes `#!/usr/bin/env bash\r` and the guest fails with
# `env: 'bash\r': No such file or directory`. Force LF for everything that runs in
# the capsule, regardless of the dev host's autocrlf setting. Windows shims stay CRLF.
*.sh        text eol=lf
*.py        text eol=lf
*.html      text eol=lf
*.conf      text eol=lf
*.args      text eol=lf
Dockerfile  text eol=lf
*.command   text eol=lf
*.bat       text eol=crlf
*.ps1       text eol=crlf
